name: Brilliant Button Bracelet
description: some days you dont feel like being all 'bright colours and sunshine and smiles'. if you're having one of those days, this bracelet is for you. mainly made up of brown, black, grey and white buttons (with a tiny red one thrown in, just to be cheeky) , its absolutely perfect for those 'just dont look at me' days. all buttons are vintage (and a fair few look as if they've been pinched from mums coats), so expect some wear and tear on a few of the buttons, but i think that adds to the charm. handmade in my bedroom, someplace, UK

name: Very Vintage Pearl Earrings
description: a pair of gorgeous vintage (i think!) goldtone (i dont think they're REAL gold, but they're beautiful) earrings with pearl detail. absolutely beautiful, but i cant see myself wearing them, dangly earrings arent my thing. in fantastic condition, they've been lurking in a box somewhere in my room for who knows how long.

name: 18 Inch Pretty Pearl Necklace
description: A stunning white imitation pearl necklace. I hate to part with it, but i know i'll never wear it, i managed to buy seven pearl necklaces and some have just got to go. This one measures 18 inches, see my other items for the 16 inch necklace.

name: 16 Inch Pretty Pearl Necklace
description: A stunning white imitation pearl necklace. I hate to part with it, but i know i'll never wear it, i managed to buy seven pearl necklaces and some have just got to go. This one measures 16 inches, see my other items for the 18 inch necklace.

name: Gorgeous Vintage Red Polka Dot Dress
description: i got this little beauty off ebay a while back, but i've only worn it about twice, which is a shame because its such a nice dress, it needs rehoming to somebody who will wear it all the time. i think its vintage, it was listed as so when i bought it, but i'm not 100%, either way, its a gorgeous piece. not too sure on the sizing, i'd say it'd fit from a 10 to a 14 easily, as the back part is elasticated. two huge pockets you can hide your sweets in, and the bottom half is massive, loads of material, absolutely brilliant for twirling about in.
